        "name": [
          "Response to Allow editing of bookmark/reply titles"
        ],
        "in-reply-to": [
          "https://github.com/jamesvandyne/tanzawa/issues"
        ],
        "published": [
          "2022-12-02T23:51:29.780743+00:00"
        ],
        "author": [
          {
            "type": [
              "h-card"
            ],
            "properties": {
              "photo": [
                {
                  "value": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/38fc6c615f36a579152118d7abf2e55b?d=mm&r=g&s=80 2x",
                  "alt": ""
                }
              ],
              "url": [
                "https://jamesvandyne.com/author/jamesvandyne/"
              ],
              "uid": [
                "https://jamesvandyne.com/author/jamesvandyne/"
              ],
              "name": [
                "James"
              ]
            },
            "value": "James"
          }
        ],
        "content": [
          {
            "html": "<blockquote>Tanzawa is a blogging system designed for the IndieWeb that focuses on sustainability. - Issues ¬∑ jamesvandyne/tanzawa</blockquote>\n        <div>\n<strong>Problem<br></strong>It's currently not possible to edit the title of bookmarks / replies without using the Django admin. This is an issue because sometimes the title contains meta information that you wouldn't want to appear in a comment / blog post.<br><br><figure class=\"attachment attachment--preview attachment--png\" data-trix-attachment='{\"contentType\":\"image/png\",\"filename\":\"image.png\",\"filesize\":36600,\"height\":208,\"href\":\"https://jamesvandyne.com/files/b5ef2cc8-63c4-48d8-9118-db3705bedadb?content-disposition=attachment\",\"url\":\"https://jamesvandyne.com/files/b5ef2cc8-63c4-48d8-9118-db3705bedadb\",\"width\":910}' data-trix-attributes='{\"caption\":\"An example title when posting a new issue from Tanzawa\",\"presentation\":\"gallery\"}' data-trix-content-type=\"image/png\"><a href=\"https://jamesvandyne.com/files/b5ef2cc8-63c4-48d8-9118-db3705bedadb?content-disposition=attachment\"><picture>\n<source srcset=\"https://jamesvandyne.com/files/b5ef2cc8-63c4-48d8-9118-db3705bedadb?f=image/webp\" type=\"image/webp\"></source>\n<img height=\"208\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://jamesvandyne.com/files/b5ef2cc8-63c4-48d8-9118-db3705bedadb\" width=\"910\">\n</picture><figcaption class=\"attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited\">An example title when posting a new issue from Tanzawa</figcaption></a></figure><br><br>This is especially true as I try to experiment with creating Tanzawa issues on my blog and backfeeding all comments, with the goal of effectively keeping the \"lab notebook\" of the GitHub issues to also be on my website.<br><br><strong>Success</strong><br>There is an edit button that, when clicked, allows you to edit the the title. <br><br><strong>Implementation Details<br></strong>This should be implemented using htmx and act as the first page to allow us to remove turbo from Tanzawa.</div>",
            "value": "Tanzawa is a blogging system designed for the IndieWeb that focuses on sustainability. - Issues ¬∑ jamesvandyne/tanzawa\n        ProblemIt's currently not possible to edit the title of bookmarks / replies without using the Django admin. This is an issue because sometimes the title contains meta information that you wouldn't want to appear in a comment / blog post.\n\n https://jamesvandyne.com/files/b5ef2cc8-63c4-48d8-9118-db3705bedadb \nAn example title when posting a new issue from TanzawaThis is especially true as I try to experiment with creating Tanzawa issues on my blog and backfeeding all comments, with the goal of effectively keeping the \"lab notebook\" of the GitHub issues to also be on my website.SuccessThere is an edit button that, when clicked, allows you to edit the the title. Implementation DetailsThis should be implemented using htmx and act as the first page to allow us to remove turbo from Tanzawa."
          }
        ],
        "url": [
          "https://jamesvandyne.com/852667ce-9821-4722-a057-48eb8f74ba97"
        ]
      }
